(98,  12, 'faq',  'a:2:{s:12:\"faq-question\";s:15:\"What is an ETF?\";s:10:\"faq-answer\";s:174:\"ETF stands for Exchange Traded Fund. An ETF is a fund that trades like a stock but has the diversification of a Mutual Fund. An ETF also tracks the performance of an index.\r\n\";}'),
(99,  12, 'faq',  'a:2:{s:12:\"faq-question\";s:16:\"What is XT Misr?\";s:10:\"faq-answer\";s:262:\"XT Misr is an ETF that is listed and traded on the Egyptian Exchange and tracks the performance of the EGX30 Index (Egypt’s leading index). It is a great easy investment tool offering access to the booming Egyptian economy with diversification and liquidity.\r\n\";}'),
(100, 12, 'faq',  'a:2:{s:12:\"faq-question\";s:24:\"What is the EGX30 Index?\";s:10:\"faq-answer\";s:136:\"The EGX 30 Index comprises of the 30 largest market cap weighted and most liquid companies listed and traded on the Egyptian Exchange.\r\n\";}'),
(101, 12, 'faq',  'a:2:{s:12:\"faq-question\";s:55:\"What is the quote of XT Misr on Mubasher and Bloomberg?\";s:10:\"faq-answer\";s:58:\"The XT Misr quote on Mubasher and Bloomberg is EGX30ETF.\r\n\";}'),
(102, 12, 'faq',  'a:2:{s:12:\"faq-question\";s:21:\"How do I buy XT Misr?\";s:10:\"faq-answer\";s:180:\"Like any share in the stock market, investors can easily buy XT Misr shares through a broker or online anytime during the trading hours of the Egyptian Exchange (10:00am-2:30pm).\r\n\";}'),
(103, 12, 'faq',  'a:2:{s:12:\"faq-question\";s:36:\"What do I need to invest in XT Misr?\";s:10:\"faq-answer\";s:71:\"All you need to invest in XT Misr are brokerage and custody accounts.\r\n\";}'),
(104, 12, 'faq',  'a:2:{s:12:\"faq-question\";s:76:\"What do I do if I have no broker and have never traded in the equity market?\";s:10:\"faq-answer\";s:337:\"You will need to open custody and brokerage accounts with Beltone Financial. Please give me your email to send you the necessary account opening forms and additional paperwork required. This usually requires an identity card for Egyptian residents and a document to verify information provided by client ie. Utility bill or phone bill.\r\n\";}'),
(105, 12, 'faq',  'a:2:{s:12:\"faq-question\";s:82:\"Why should I buy XT Misr? Why invest in XT Misr? What are the benefits of XT Misr?\";s:10:\"faq-answer\";s:791:\"XT Misr is a great investment opportunity for investors interested in benefitting from Egypt’s economic recovery without having to track and trade multiple individual companies. There are 5 main benefits for investing in XT Misr. Flexibility Trades like a share on the stock exchange No minimum investment requirements Efficiency Replicates the performance of a basket of securities without the hassle of buying the underlying securities No sales charge and low management fees Transparency Prices can be viewed and traded at any time during the trading hours of the EGX Basket of constituents are disclosed daily on Beltone Financials website Diversification Instant exposure to a portfolio of sectors and stocks Liquidity Market makers buy and sell the ETF to ensure constant liquidity\r\n\";}'),
(106, 12, 'faq',  'a:2:{s:12:\"faq-question\";s:41:\"What are the expected returns of XT Misr?\";s:10:\"faq-answer\";s:169:\"The return of XT Misr should mimic (replicate, track, correspond) the performance of the EGX 30 index in addition to semi-annual dividend distributions after expenses.\r\n\";}'),
(107, 12, 'faq',  'a:2:{s:12:\"faq-question\";s:30:\"What are the risks of XT Misr?\";s:10:\"faq-answer\";s:91:\"The risk is, as with any stock, XT Misr is subject to market moves. It can go up or down.\r\n\";}'),
(108, 12, 'faq',  'a:2:{s:12:\"faq-question\";s:49:\"What is the minimum investment value for XT Misr?\";s:10:\"faq-answer\";s:83:\"There is no minimum to investing in XT-Misr. You can buy as much as 1 share only.\r\n\";}'),
(109, 12, 'faq',  'a:2:{s:12:\"faq-question\";s:39:\"How much money should I put in the ETF?\";s:10:\"faq-answer\";s:190:\"This truly depends on your risk return profile. Given that XT Misr is an investment in the stock market we do not recommend to put all your savings as the price is subject to market moves.\r\n\";}'),
(110, 12, 'faq',  'a:2:{s:12:\"faq-question\";s:105:\"What is the difference between a mutual fund and an ETF? What if I already hold shares in XX Mutual Fund?\";s:10:\"faq-answer\";s:609:\"The biggest difference between an XT Misr and a Mutual Fund is that the shares of the ETF are listed and trading on the Egyptian Stock Exchange with real time pricing and you can trade it via a broker. Another important difference is that XT Misr has no minimum subscription, you can buy just one share with no subscription or redemption fees unlike Mutual Funds that have minimum subscription amounts and subscription redemption fees. XT Misr discloses daily the weights of the fund constituents on a daily basis vs. limited disclosure for mutual funds. XT Misr also has lower fees than an Investment Fund.\r\n\";}'),
(111, 12, 'faq',  'a:2:{s:12:\"faq-question\";s:65:\"How long do I need to hold XT Misr shares before I can sell them?\";s:10:\"faq-answer\";s:157:\"Like investing in shares, you can trade XT-Misr actively to take short term profit opportunities, or you can hold XT-Misr shares as a long term investment.\r\n\";}'),
(112, 12, 'faq',  'a:2:{s:12:\"faq-question\";s:43:\"How are XT Misr share transactions settled?\";s:10:\"faq-answer\";s:64:\"T+2: the same settlement cycle of their underlying securities.\r\n\";}'),
(113, 12, 'faq',  'a:2:{s:12:\"faq-question\";s:44:\"What determines the price of XT-Misr Shares?\";s:10:\"faq-answer\";s:391:\"Supply and demand forces throughout the trading session will determine XT Misr’s share price. The Net Asset Value (NAV) is calculated & announced after the session based on the Fund holdings and accrued daily expenses. In addition, for transparency purposes, on the Beltone Financial website you can find an indicative NAV that is updated throughout the trading day using instant prices.\r\n\";}'),
(114, 12, 'faq',  'a:2:{s:12:\"faq-question\";s:29:\"What are the fees of XT Misr?\";s:10:\"faq-answer\";s:206:\"Investors pay brokerage commission, trading and clearing fees just like buying and selling any other share. If you choose to work with Beltone Brokerage, there is a 10% discount on commission for XT Misr.\r\n\";}'),
(115, 12, 'faq',  'a:2:{s:12:\"faq-question\";s:22:\"Is XT Misr tax exempt?\";s:10:\"faq-answer\";s:72:\"The burden of paying capital gains taxes is removed from the investor.\r\n\";}'),
(116, 12, 'faq',  'a:2:{s:12:\"faq-question\";s:64:\"What happens if I buy the shares at a higher price than the NAV?\";s:10:\"faq-answer\";s:123:\"Unfortunately, there is not much than can be done except for sell at or above your par value so as to not realize losses.\r\n\";}'),
(117, 12, 'faq',  'a:2:{s:12:\"faq-question\";s:78:\"Where can I find the price of the NAV (indicative NAV) during the trading day?\";s:10:\"faq-answer\";s:235:\"The indicative NAV of XT Misr is available throughout the trading day on the Beltone Financial website in the asset management section under funds. http://www.beltonefinancial.com/egx30etf Or on the XT Misr website on the below link.\r\n\";}'),
(118, 12, 'faq',  'a:2:{s:12:\"faq-question\";s:75:\"Why isn’t the ETF trading in parallel with the EGX 30, especially % wise?\";s:10:\"faq-answer\";s:405:\"The price of the ETF on the stock exchange is depends on the prices bid and offered by the buyer and seller in the market and market expectations. The best way to check whether the ETF share is trading at a discount or premium to the EGX30 is by checking the indicative NAV on Beltone’s website. According to regulations, you can track correlation of the performance of XT Misr vs. EGX30 over 60 days.\r\n\";}'),
(119, 12, 'faq',  'a:2:{s:12:\"faq-question\";s:68:\"Will it be public information, how many shares the market maker has?\";s:10:\"faq-answer\";s:79:\"No, the number of shares the market maker has will not be public information.\r\n\";}'),
(120, 12, 'faq',  'a:2:{s:12:\"faq-question\";s:36:\"What is the maximum size of XT Misr?\";s:10:\"faq-answer\";s:143:\"The maximum size can be up to 50x the seed capital, which currently is EGP 5million. Therefore, EGP250million is the maximum size of XT Misr.\r\n\";}'),
(121, 12, 'faq',  'a:2:{s:12:\"faq-question\";s:84:\"Can the market maker create as much as they want, and can they sell before creating?\";s:10:\"faq-answer\";s:200:\"Yes, they can, as long as they provide the basket of underlying stocks by the end of day. Yes, the market maker can sell before creating but whatever they sell is always covered and ensured by MCDR.\r\n\";}'),
(122, 12, 'faq',  'a:2:{s:12:\"faq-question\";s:142:\"Is there an equation to calculate the price of the ETF to the EGX 30, meaning if the ETF is trading at 10.20 what is that to the egx 30 9,500?\";s:10:\"faq-answer\";s:92:\"The day the price of XT Misr was EGP10, the index value was XX (closing value of Tuesday).\r\n\";}'),
(123, 12, 'faq',  'a:2:{s:12:\"faq-question\";s:204:\"If the EGX 30 is going up, but there is selling pressure on the ETF; will the market maker/fund buy in the etf to make it reach the same value as the index? Same question if it’s the opposite situation.\";s:10:\"faq-answer\";s:174:\"The market maker is different than the fund. In this case, there is an arbitrage opportunity in the market, where the market maker and anyone else can take advantage of it.\r\n\";}'),
